	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />powerpak mod was pretty simple I just swapped the chip that was swapped here
<br />
<br /><a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=4016&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;start=0" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=4016&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;start=0</a>
<br />
<br />Also the s-video and composite conversion aren't external they're internal.
<br />
<br />av famicom isn't ultra rare.  Before I installed this mod it outputted nothing on the s-video / rgb pins of the multi av port.
<br />
<br />You can do this mod on any model nes or famicom but the av famicom has an improved pcb that removes a lot of the video interference.  I built a rgb nes before making this and the video jailbar interference was really annoying.
<br />
<br />I posted a lot of questions a long time ago and never got many answers so I went looking for answers elsewhere.
<br />
<br />As for the poor audio mixing I built a couple of nes stereo sound mods I found on the net and installed them on the av famicom.  Games that didn't have advanced audio chips sounded great but games like castlevania 3 j suddenly the sound effects were much louder than the music.
<br />
<br />I don't mind explaining what was done I just figured I'd wait for people to ask questions before going into detail.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
